Vice President Mike Pence led a discussion with the chief executives and senior leaders of approximately 50 states, territories, and the White House Coronavirus Task Force to discuss local, state, and federal COVID-19 response and recovery efforts. They discussed the positive news of the FDA's emergency use authorization (EUA) for the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine and the shipments of the initial allocations of the vaccine. The Vice President also discussed ongoing efforts to mitigate and respond to COVID-19, vaccine distribution and administration planning, and updates on medical supply chain management efforts. FDA Commissioner Dr. Hahn and CDC Director Redfield provided updates on vaccine and therapeutic developments, while Secretary Azar provided updates on Moderna's vaccine trial and coordination with states. General Perna provided an update on vaccine distribution planning, and Administrator Verma discussed CMS' strategy to enhance hospital capacity and vaccination in dialysis centers. Ambassador Birx provided an update on data and trends from across the nation. The Trump Administration has organized and hosted 44 governors-only briefings since January 2020 to drive effective communication and collaboration between the federal and state levels.